Author: TheGemologist#6023
Content: Other question that may sound dumb.. If i set a higher limit, than my BTC will be spent faster because more hash is being used and i will spend less time on the pool, so will i receive less reward ? Is it better to keep a lower limit of hash and stay longer on the pool or this doesnt matter?

Author: mrlynch#5735
Content: If you're mining on piratepool you get the shares so it doesn't really matter, however a good strategy is to have high hash power when difficulty is low as you'll get more rewards

Author: mrlynch#5735
Content: Basically you need to monitor the network difficulty and when it's low you increase the limit on nh, not the bid. When diff goes up you lower the limit back to 0.1

Author: mrlynch#5735
Content: That way you make most of your btc on nh

Author: mrlynch#5735
Content: Or you can be a lazy git like me, set it low and let her rip ğŸ˜‚
